  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    InvalidSequenceException
    This exception is only caused when characters are in an invalid sequence.
    LengthException
    This exception is only caused when you have a string that is not the correct length.
    NoDigitException
    This exception should only be caused when a string does not contain a digit.
    NoLowerAlphaException
    This exception should only occur when a string does not contain any lowercase letters.
    NoSpecialSymbolException
    This Exception should only occur when a String Contains no special symbols.
    NoUpperAlphaException
    This exception should only occur when the String does not contain any uppercase letters.
    PasswordException
    This exception isn't directly called, but is a superclass of all other exceptions in this package.
    UnmatchedException
    This exception should occur when two strings do not match, so if the strings are not equal to each other Example: "MikE" to "Mike", "Random" to "Something else", "Cool" to "Not"
